    <note>She Yanzhi [405] From a great lineage (dazu) of Yunzhong. Starting with his ancestors in the Five Dynasties (&amp; earlier during the Northern Wei), each generation was represented by high military officers who distinguished themselves in every Northern Song war. The main branch of the lineage served as the successive hereditary prefects of Fuzhou on the Shanxi-Mongolian border and military governors of the region. When Qin(1) Gui [8008] became chief minister, he exiled Yanzhi to Binzhou (where I identify his latest address) in Hunan because he had been a client of Zhao(1) Ding [8024]. XNYL, 94.6a, 174.5a; Guangdong TZ, 15.9a. CBD, 2, 1077.</note>
